<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Crime Prevention Articles on Toronto Police Service</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/feed</link><description></description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/feed"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 30 Nov 2018 01:19:21 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Frauds Against Seniors</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/frauds-against-seniors/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Scams targeting older people are now called “the crime of the 21st century”, as they have become so widespread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;Seniors are actively pursued by fraudsters for many reasons, including perceived accessibility, vulnerability and reluctance to report this crime. Social isolation is also a big risk factor.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 30 Nov 2018 01:09:17 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/frauds-against-seniors/</guid></item><item><title>Identity Theft</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/identity-theft-1/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Identity theft can happen to anyone. This rapidly growing crime affects more people every day in Toronto and around the world.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;Yet, surprisingly most people think it will not happen to them. Reasons for this increase include the proliferation of card skimming devices and the hacking of computers.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 29 Nov 2018 23:03:18 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/identity-theft-1/</guid></item><item><title>Are You in an Abusive Relationship?</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/are-you-in-an-abusive-relationship/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Healthy relationships are based on love, trust and respect for each other.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unhealthy relationships typically start with behaviour that is obsessive in nature and can quickly lead to abuse.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class="textbox" style="margin: 0cm; margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 07 Nov 2018 15:32:25 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/are-you-in-an-abusive-relationship/</guid></item><item><title>Transit Safety</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/transit-safety/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;PLAN AHEAD – use common sense and good judgment. Think about where you are going and plan your route before you leave. Consider:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir="ltr"&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The time of day&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the next bus is scheduled&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;How can you avoid walking through uninhabited or badly lit areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 08 Nov 2018 19:16:14 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/transit-safety/</guid></item><item><title>Home Security</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/home-security/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Home security can be as effective as you make it. Do not leave the responsibility for your safety and security to others. REDUCE YOUR RISK by practicing the crime prevention strategies outlined in this pamphlet. Together, you and your neighbours can work towards reducing crime in your area.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 30 Nov 2018 01:06:02 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/home-security/</guid></item><item><title>Auto Crimes</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/auto-crimes-1/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;By taking simple precautions, you can dramatically reduce the risk of vehicle theft or the loss of property from your vehicle.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 08 Nov 2018 17:33:31 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/auto-crimes-1/</guid></item><item><title>Holiday Safety &amp; Travel Tips</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/holiday-safety-travel-tips/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;As we all have the potential to be victims of crime, it is important to remember that Safety Starts With YOU!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;By taking a few precautions, each of us can REDUCE THE RISK of being victimized by eliminating the opportunity during the holiday season or while on vacatio&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 30 Nov 2018 01:11:27 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/holiday-safety-travel-tips/</guid></item><item><title>Bicycle Safety &amp; Theft Prevention</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/bicycle-safety-and-theft-prevention/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;But it is important to remember that a bicycle is not a toy - a bicycle is a vehicle under The Highway Traffic Act and thousands are stolen each year.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 09 Nov 2018 03:08:14 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/bicycle-safety-and-theft-prevention/</guid></item><item><title>Human Trafficking Avoidance</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/human-trafficking-avoidance/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Human Trafficking is the forced exploitation of another person typically for sexual purposes. Human traffickers seek out young, particularly high school aged, teens who they groom and exercise control over by a variety of means including deception, threats, manipulation and violence.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;Human trafficking is highly profitable activity that often involves gang members.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 30 Nov 2018 00:53:21 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/human-trafficking-avoidance/</guid></item><item><title>Distraction Theft</title><link>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/distraction-theft/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Victims of distraction theft are often chosen because they are elderly, trusting, and may speak little or no English.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;The offenders generally target people who are walking or sitting alone in public or on their own property. The offenders look for exposed jewellery or may just assume their target is likely wearing it.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 30 Nov 2018 01:19:21 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.tps.ca/crime-prevention/distraction-theft/</guid></item></channel></rss>
```
